bio/stat-gen workloads relegated to cpu01 + gpu02 ("shared research pool")

Structural problem with the proposal:
Cluster has no parallel-compute infrastructure — no Lustre/GPFS/BeeGFS, no RDMA fabric between compute nodes (only NetApp filer has RDMA enabled, but compute nodes have no HCAs, no InfiniBand/RoCE switch), no MPI runtime. NetApp NFSv4.1 over TCP + nconnect + 1MB transfer is the storage path.
The author's dev-cpu (Both) and interactive (Both) partitions assume pool-mode scheduling (Slurm picks which of two nodes runs a job). The "fall-back of services from cgpu01 to gpu01" assumes auto-failover Slurm can't provide. None of the workloads in the proposal actually need cross-node parallelism — all are single-node — but the partition design was written as if they could span nodes.
