Operational gotchas learned this session

Apptainer on Ubuntu 24.04 noble — not in main universe repo, only Go library packages. Use ppa:apptainer/ppa. Same path on all nodes for fleet consistency.
APPTAINER_CACHEDIR and APPTAINER_TMPDIR matter — defaults are ~/.apptainer/cache and /tmp; both can fill OS disk. Always point at /scratch. Should become a /etc/profile.d/apptainer-defaults.sh fleet-wide.
SIFs stay on /scratch pre-NetApp — /scratch/cluster-software/containers/. After NetApp lands, rsync to /software/containers/. SIFs are immutable artifacts — migration is a file copy, not a rebuild. Apptainer cache stays on local /scratch forever, never migrate it to NetApp.
sacctmgr show association tree is the authoritative view of account hierarchy — show account with ParentName column lies (shows empty ParentName when nesting is correct).
sacctmgr modify account ... set parent= — when it returns "Request didn't affect anything", verify with tree view; the state may already be correct.
Slurm requires --account= on submission — AccountingStorageEnforce=associations is on. Default account behavior was uncertain; admin pattern is to be in research parent.
Prolog/Epilog scripts in slurm.conf must either exist or be commented out — non-existent scripts cause every job to drain the node with Reason=Prolog error. PrologFlags=Contain stays valid without a Prolog script.
slurm.conf must be byte-identical fleet-wide — register_gpu_nodes.sh (Nick's script, runs from cpu01) handles install + munge.key + config push + daemon restart in one go.
Orphan slurmd after failed restart — systemctl restart slurmd can leave a daemon running if it was mid-prolog-failure when SIGTERM arrived. Symptom: "Address already in use" on port 6818. Fix: find PID via ps aux | grep slurmd, kill it manually, then systemctl start slurmd.

